<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!-- Inherited entitlements for ALL helper processes (Renderer / GPU /
       Plugin). electron-builder's `mac.entitlementsInherit` is a single
       plist applied uniformly to every helper bundle — there is no
       built-in per-helper-type configuration as of electron-builder
       26.8.1. The Renderer helper requires com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit
       (V8 JIT) and com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory
       to function; granting these to GPU / Plugin helpers is a known
       upstream-imposed over-grant. Trigger to revisit: electron-builder
       adds per-helper-type entitlement support (track via Dependabot once
       github-actions ecosystem is enabled), or migrate to a customSign
       callback that signs each helper bundle individually with a tighter
       plist.

       FORBIDDEN under all circumstances (CI guard at checks.yml:136-144
       fails the build if either string appears here):
         - com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
         - com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables -->
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
  <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
